Create a `reset.css` stylesheet to remove broswer default styling.
http://meyerweb.com/eric/tools/css/reset/

Create stylesheets for each target device (phone, tablet, desktop).

Set up media queries for tablet and desktop.
@media only screen and (min-width: 641px) {
} /*end of the media query*/
(Note: phone-default.css won't have any media query since all the css rules in it are meant to apply to all devices)

Ensure phones don't lie about their width:
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1">

Prevent font sizes to change when switching from portrait to landscape modes.
html {-webkit-text-size-adjust: none; }


/*----------- apply a natural box layout model to all elements --------------*/
Older browsers have a problem handling block elements defined with width:50%, margin:0, and padding:5% because the padding in fact expands the width to 60%, whereas
newer browsers handle this correctly by maintaining a width of 50%.  Apply the following so that older browsers handle this properly without expansion.
Also note that `-moz-box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-box-sizing: border-box;` are only needed for really really old browsers.
* {box-sizing: border-box; -moz-box-sizing: border-box; -webkit-box-sizing: border-box;  }


***** SCRIPT TO HELP OLD IE (IE 8 and older) UNDERSTAND HTML5 AND MEDIA QUERIES
<!--[if lt IE 9]>
	<script src="http://html5shim.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/html5.js"></script>
	<script src="http://css3-mediaqueries-js.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/css3-mediaqueries.js"></script>
<![endif]-->